1
00:00:05,621 --> 00:00:08,323
♪

2
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:08,327
[ROOSTER CALLING]

3
00:01:08,351 --> 00:01:09,784
KARA: Yahoo!

4
00:01:10,787 --> 00:01:13,121
Spring break at last.

5
00:01:13,790 --> 00:01:14,790
[YELPS]

6
00:01:21,097 --> 00:01:22,630
[DOOR SLAMS]

7
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:25,767
[DOOR SLAMS]

8
00:01:28,371 --> 00:01:30,817
So long, Snoozeville. Hello, Metropolis.

9
00:01:30,841 --> 00:01:32,685
Just a minute, little lady.

10
00:01:32,709 --> 00:01:34,487
You still have your chores.

11
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:35,576
Done...

12
00:01:37,747 --> 00:01:39,257
[CHICKENS CLUCKING]

13
00:01:39,281 --> 00:01:40,281
And done.

14
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:44,196
Kara, you know how that upsets the chickens.

15
00:01:44,220 --> 00:01:46,182
Good thing I didn't ask her to milk the cow.

16
00:01:46,206 --> 00:01:48,539
[COW MOOS]

17
00:01:49,576 --> 00:01:51,508
Oops.

18
00:01:55,332 --> 00:01:57,142
I hope you'll try to act more normal

19
00:01:57,166 --> 00:01:59,395
while you're staying with Clark.

20
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:03,232
You know how he likes to keep a low profile.

21
00:02:03,256 --> 00:02:06,152
No offense, but what's so great about being normal?

22
00:02:06,176 --> 00:02:07,953
Now see here.

23
00:02:07,977 --> 00:02:09,522
If it's good enough for us humans,

24
00:02:09,546 --> 00:02:10,772
it's good enough for you.

25
00:02:10,796 --> 00:02:11,824
Mmm-mwah.

26
00:02:11,848 --> 00:02:13,948
If you say so.

27
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:27,706
I can't wait.

28
00:02:27,730 --> 00:02:29,242
The bus is just a mile away.

29
00:02:29,266 --> 00:02:31,344
How do you kn...?

30
00:02:31,368 --> 00:02:32,667
Oh, never mind.

31
00:02:33,203 --> 00:02:34,335
Hey, Kara.

32
00:02:35,304 --> 00:02:36,682
Hey, Owen.

33
00:02:36,706 --> 00:02:38,734
Your folks said you were going to Metropolis,

34
00:02:38,758 --> 00:02:41,092
so I brought you something to read on your trip.

35
00:02:42,729 --> 00:02:44,628
Comic books?

36
00:02:45,798 --> 00:02:47,043
[WHISPERS] Be nice.

37
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:48,094
Thanks.

38
00:02:48,118 --> 00:02:49,078
No problem.

39
00:02:49,102 --> 00:02:50,679
Uh, maybe you could drop me a post card

40
00:02:50,703 --> 00:02:51,764
from the big city.

41
00:02:51,788 --> 00:02:54,883
Gee, I'm gonna be pretty busy.

42
00:02:54,907 --> 00:02:56,919
Sure.

43
00:02:56,943 --> 00:02:58,004
Oh, darn, here's the bus.

44
00:02:58,028 --> 00:02:59,028
See ya.

45
00:03:00,579 --> 00:03:02,313
Have fun, sweetie.

46
00:03:08,337 --> 00:03:10,721
♪

47
00:03:12,675 --> 00:03:13,891
Oh, sorry.

48
00:03:18,130 --> 00:03:19,213
Friendly guy.

49
00:03:32,095 --> 00:03:33,772
Weird.

50
00:03:33,796 --> 00:03:34,929
Heh.

51
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:37,943
<i>Spider Powers.</i>

52
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:39,366
Ew!

53
00:03:40,703 --> 00:03:42,031
KARA: <i>Dear Ma and Pa,</i>

54
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:44,700
<i>So far, I've been having a blast in Metropolis.</i>

55
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:46,202
<i>Clark's been showing me the sights</i>

56
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:48,370
<i>and introducing me to all the local celebrities.</i>

57
00:03:48,394 --> 00:03:50,589
<i>Even better, Lois Lane's been taking me with her</i>

58
00:03:50,613 --> 00:03:52,324
<i>to all the major press events.</i>

59
00:03:52,348 --> 00:03:55,611
<i>The Metropolis Meteor has made me their honorary bat girl.</i>

60
00:03:55,635 --> 00:03:57,651
<i>Won't Barbara be jealous.</i>

61
00:04:02,408 --> 00:04:04,653
<i>Naturally, Supergirl's been seeing her share</i>

62
00:04:04,677 --> 00:04:07,072
<i>of big-city action too.</i>

63
00:04:07,096 --> 00:04:09,508
You're out of your league, Super Snot.

64
00:04:09,532 --> 00:04:11,394
If I was too hot for Superman,

65
00:04:11,418 --> 00:04:13,746
I'll roast you like a marshmallow.

66
00:04:13,770 --> 00:04:14,935
[GRUNTS]

67
00:04:16,306 --> 00:04:17,921
You're all hot air, Volcana.

68
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:20,941
[GRUNTING]

69
00:04:23,162 --> 00:04:26,208
Is it hot in here, or is it just me?

70
00:04:26,232 --> 00:04:27,665
[GRUNTS]

71
00:04:30,636 --> 00:04:31,613
Hot?

72
00:04:31,637 --> 00:04:33,231
I think I'm getting frostbite.

73
00:04:33,255 --> 00:04:35,872
It's your cremation, kiddo.

74
00:04:37,076 --> 00:04:38,542
[VOLCANA SCREAMING]

75
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:42,908
KARA: <i>Well, that's all for now.</i>

76
00:04:42,932 --> 00:04:44,509
<i>See ya in a couple days.</i>

77
00:04:44,533 --> 00:04:46,429
<i>Love, Kara.</i>

78
00:04:46,453 --> 00:04:49,365
Going back to Smallville is sad enough.

79
00:04:49,389 --> 00:04:51,405
But do I have to take the bus again?

80
00:04:53,108 --> 00:04:55,537
You know how important it is we keep a low profile.

81
00:04:55,561 --> 00:04:57,656
Besides, it's only two days.

82
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,208
You get to see a lot of the country

83
00:04:59,232 --> 00:05:01,465
and meet some interesting people.

84
00:05:03,153 --> 00:05:05,247
CLARK: <i>It'll be fun.</i>

85
00:05:05,271 --> 00:05:06,315
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:05:06,339 --> 00:05:07,916
[BABY CRYING]

87
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:09,451
"Fun," he said.

88
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:11,186
Look at that field, Eugene.

89
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:13,555
Would you say those are rutabagas or turnips?

90
00:05:13,579 --> 00:05:15,023
I'd say turnips.

91
00:05:15,047 --> 00:05:16,124
WOMAN: Really?

92
00:05:16,148 --> 00:05:17,877
I'd swear they were rutabagas.

93
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:19,845
No, Vina, them's turnips.

94
00:05:19,869 --> 00:05:22,514
Now, Eugene, I know rutabagas and I know turnips,

95
00:05:22,538 --> 00:05:25,600
and those don't look like no turnips I've ever seen.

96
00:05:25,624 --> 00:05:26,868
Brain imploding.

97
00:05:26,892 --> 00:05:28,437
Shutting down.

98
00:05:28,461 --> 00:05:30,840
Young lady, maybe you can settle this.

99
00:05:30,864 --> 00:05:32,107
You see that field out there?

100
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:34,710
Would you say those are rutabagas or turnips?

101
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:37,262
I'm so out of here.

102
00:05:37,286 --> 00:05:38,414
[DINGS]

103
00:05:38,438 --> 00:05:39,570
My stop.

104
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:41,355
Out here?

105
00:05:43,526 --> 00:05:45,520
This is the middle of nowhere.

106
00:05:45,544 --> 00:05:47,744
I know. It's called Kansas.

107
00:05:48,932 --> 00:05:50,459
EUGENE: What did she say, Vina?

108
00:05:50,483 --> 00:05:53,116
I think she went out to check.

109
00:06:05,531 --> 00:06:08,110
I'm home.

110
00:06:08,134 --> 00:06:09,778
Ma?

111
00:06:09,802 --> 00:06:11,363
Pa?

112
00:06:11,387 --> 00:06:12,931
[MEOWS]

113
00:06:12,955 --> 00:06:14,867
Hey, Streaky.

114
00:06:14,891 --> 00:06:16,268
Miss me?

115
00:06:16,292 --> 00:06:17,969
[MEOWS]

116
00:06:17,993 --> 00:06:19,438
What's the matter?

117
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:20,439
No one feed you today?

118
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:21,657
JONATHAN: Kara?

119
00:06:21,681 --> 00:06:23,642
Oh, hi, guys.

120
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:24,643
[GROWLING]

121
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:26,111
Streaky!

122
00:06:26,135 --> 00:06:27,329
What's gotten into him?

123
00:06:27,353 --> 00:06:28,330
You're early.

124
00:06:28,354 --> 00:06:29,882
Well, I didn't want you

125
00:06:29,906 --> 00:06:32,134
making a run to the bus station on my account.

126
00:06:32,158 --> 00:06:34,736
But we were going to pick you up and take you some place special.

127
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,937
KARA: Let me guess.

128
00:06:35,961 --> 00:06:37,939
It's all-you-can-eat night at the Pig Pit?

129
00:06:37,963 --> 00:06:38,980
You'll see.

130
00:06:39,882 --> 00:06:40,993
KARA: Wow.

131
00:06:41,017 --> 00:06:42,978
The town is deader than usual.

132
00:06:43,002 --> 00:06:44,613
Where is everybody?

133
00:06:44,637 --> 00:06:45,637
Patience.

134
00:06:51,543 --> 00:06:52,860
Here we are.

135
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,261
Don't tell me the circus is back so soon.

136
00:06:59,285 --> 00:07:01,563
No, it's much better than that.

137
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:03,199
Hey, Owen. What's up?

138
00:07:03,223 --> 00:07:04,300
Unity.

139
00:07:04,324 --> 00:07:05,751
Unity? What's that?

140
00:07:05,775 --> 00:07:07,725
New band?

141
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:13,091
[GASPS]

142
00:07:13,115 --> 00:07:15,544
There you are, Jonathan and Martha.

143
00:07:15,568 --> 00:07:17,580
We've been waiting for you.

144
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:22,084
Ah, and this must be Kara, about whom I've heard so much.

145
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:23,235
I know you.

146
00:07:23,259 --> 00:07:24,770
The man from the bus station.

147
00:07:24,794 --> 00:07:27,072
The Reverend Amos Howell at your service.

148
00:07:27,096 --> 00:07:30,476
A humble traveler spreading the word of Unity.

149
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:32,812
Which is what, exactly?

150
00:07:32,836 --> 00:07:35,181
The one true source of universal bliss.

151
00:07:35,205 --> 00:07:40,619
Nations fall and demigods fade, but only Unity is absolute,

152
00:07:40,643 --> 00:07:43,722
all-encompassing and eternal.

153
00:07:43,746 --> 00:07:45,107
Ugh.

154
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:46,925
Does Pastor Ross know about this?

155
00:07:46,949 --> 00:07:49,211
Oh, he was among the first converts.

156
00:07:49,235 --> 00:07:51,096
Your stepparents, your neighbors,

157
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:55,584
indeed everyone in Smallville has embraced the call of Unity.

158
00:07:55,608 --> 00:07:58,320
Now it is time for you to do the same.

159
00:07:58,344 --> 00:08:03,430
PEOPLE [FLATLY]: Unity. Unity. Unity. Unity.

160
00:08:09,455 --> 00:08:10,821
[GASPS]

161
00:08:15,869 --> 00:08:18,247
PEOPLE [FLATLY]: Unity. Unity. Unity. Unity.

162
00:08:18,271 --> 00:08:20,600
Welcome, Kara.

163
00:08:20,624 --> 00:08:22,157
Join us.

164
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,826
What have you done to them?

165
00:08:30,850 --> 00:08:33,902
Made them one with a greater power.

166
00:08:42,046 --> 00:08:45,580
We... <i>are</i> Unity.

167
00:08:50,554 --> 00:08:51,686
[GASPS]

168
00:08:52,389 --> 00:08:54,267
She won't get far.

169
00:08:54,291 --> 00:08:57,236
Hey, preacher!

170
00:08:57,260 --> 00:08:59,243
I'm shutting down your tent show.

171
00:09:02,616 --> 00:09:03,576
[GRUNTS]

172
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,084
[ALL GROANING]

173
00:09:10,374 --> 00:09:11,685
[GROANS]

174
00:09:11,709 --> 00:09:13,608
No!

175
00:09:18,098 --> 00:09:19,131
Wake up.

176
00:09:20,534 --> 00:09:22,812
HOWELL: It's futile.

177
00:09:22,836 --> 00:09:24,664
We are one,

178
00:09:24,688 --> 00:09:28,318
like every other being who has joined Unity.

179
00:09:28,342 --> 00:09:31,287
Planet after planet, age after age,

180
00:09:31,311 --> 00:09:35,442
Unity grows stronger with each world we touch.

181
00:09:35,466 --> 00:09:38,783
ALL: You cannot fight us.

182
00:09:46,743 --> 00:09:48,410
Unity.

183
00:09:53,834 --> 00:09:56,146
[BEEPING]

184
00:09:56,170 --> 00:09:59,316
SUPERMAN: I got here as soon as I could.

185
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:01,151
What happened?

186
00:10:01,175 --> 00:10:04,742
I told them I got a distress call from the Midwest.

187
00:10:06,630 --> 00:10:08,914
I found her with that thing sticking out of her.

188
00:10:11,401 --> 00:10:14,502
I've never seen anything like it.

189
00:10:19,943 --> 00:10:22,271
The x-rays show some kind of parasite

190
00:10:22,295 --> 00:10:23,923
wrapped around her brain stem.

191
00:10:23,947 --> 00:10:26,376
We can't remove it without killing her.

192
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,878
Ohhh.

193
00:10:28,902 --> 00:10:30,669
Mrs. Kent?

194
00:10:31,788 --> 00:10:32,887
[WHISPERS] Ma?

195
00:10:34,223 --> 00:10:37,153
Kara? Clark?

196
00:10:37,177 --> 00:10:38,154
Help me.

197
00:10:38,178 --> 00:10:40,629
[MOANING]

198
00:10:41,931 --> 00:10:43,498
What's happening to her?

199
00:10:46,553 --> 00:10:48,769
We have to run more tests.

200
00:10:50,390 --> 00:10:51,623
Come on.

201
00:10:58,766 --> 00:11:00,276
This is all my fault.

202
00:11:00,300 --> 00:11:01,861
If I'd have stayed home,

203
00:11:01,885 --> 00:11:03,329
none of this would have happened.

204
00:11:03,353 --> 00:11:04,914
You couldn't have known about this.

205
00:11:04,938 --> 00:11:06,348
But I did.

206
00:11:06,372 --> 00:11:08,083
I saw that guy come into town.

207
00:11:08,107 --> 00:11:09,469
He gave me the creeps.

208
00:11:09,493 --> 00:11:11,270
I should've checked it out,

209
00:11:11,294 --> 00:11:13,394
but I was in such a rush that I left anyway.

210
00:11:16,466 --> 00:11:17,643
We've gotta get back there.

211
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:18,811
Everyone's in danger.

212
00:11:18,835 --> 00:11:20,735
Pa, Owen, all my friends.

213
00:11:22,172 --> 00:11:23,683
I need to know what we're fighting.

214
00:11:23,707 --> 00:11:25,485
It's obviously an alien spore.

215
00:11:25,509 --> 00:11:27,437
I wanna put it under a microscope.

216
00:11:27,461 --> 00:11:28,461
Just hurry.

217
00:11:30,363 --> 00:11:32,708
The EKG doesn't lie.

218
00:11:32,732 --> 00:11:35,160
The parasite feeds off the electrical impulses

219
00:11:35,184 --> 00:11:36,334
in her nervous system.

220
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,167
Is that possible?

221
00:11:41,191 --> 00:11:43,741
It's not only possible, it's getting stronger.

222
00:11:48,782 --> 00:11:51,995
HOWELL: Supergirl has compromised our cause...

223
00:11:52,019 --> 00:11:55,682
but she cannot stop us. No one can.

224
00:11:55,706 --> 00:11:58,017
For tonight, we shall go forth into this world

225
00:11:58,041 --> 00:11:59,702
as we have done on countless others

226
00:11:59,726 --> 00:12:02,527
and spread the power of Unity.

227
00:12:15,726 --> 00:12:19,027
ALL: Unity. Unity. Unity. Unity.

228
00:12:24,501 --> 00:12:25,767
Unity.

229
00:12:28,137 --> 00:12:30,600
This tendril has an unbelievably dense cell structure.

230
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:32,852
It's hard to get a visual reading.

231
00:12:32,876 --> 00:12:34,442
Let me take a look.

232
00:12:42,085 --> 00:12:44,952
I see large mitochondria and...

233
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,384
Wait.

234
00:12:48,408 --> 00:12:49,473
Something's happening.

235
00:13:00,236 --> 00:13:02,086
[SIGHS]

236
00:13:12,232 --> 00:13:14,131
Hey, guys, any word yet?

237
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:18,664
Mrs. Kent?

238
00:13:18,688 --> 00:13:20,171
She's much better now.

239
00:13:22,543 --> 00:13:24,103
No, she's not!

240
00:13:24,127 --> 00:13:27,045
There's no greater healer than Unity.

241
00:13:28,215 --> 00:13:29,780
[SCREAMS]

242
00:13:34,219 --> 00:13:36,653
[GRUNTING]

243
00:13:52,922 --> 00:13:54,054
[BOTH GROANING]

244
00:13:54,973 --> 00:13:55,973
I'm sorry.

245
00:14:08,688 --> 00:14:11,083
MARTHA: Give in, Kara. Don't resist.

246
00:14:11,107 --> 00:14:12,584
MAN: Accept us.

247
00:14:12,608 --> 00:14:14,941
ALL: Accept Unity.

248
00:14:16,646 --> 00:14:18,286
SUPERMAN: Supergirl!

249
00:14:20,616 --> 00:14:23,099
[ALL GROANING]

250
00:14:25,404 --> 00:14:26,998
Thanks. But how did...?

251
00:14:27,022 --> 00:14:28,233
Remember when Ma woke up?

252
00:14:28,257 --> 00:14:29,506
It was the x-rays.

253
00:14:52,932 --> 00:14:57,050
[GROANING]

254
00:15:08,647 --> 00:15:10,664
Once they wake up, they should be fine.

255
00:15:11,967 --> 00:15:14,112
Sleep well, Ma.

256
00:15:14,136 --> 00:15:15,136
Let's go.

257
00:15:26,431 --> 00:15:28,576
As shadows fall in twilight,

258
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:31,062
so shall we spread across the land.

259
00:15:31,086 --> 00:15:32,197
Go now.

260
00:15:32,221 --> 00:15:35,406
Go forth and spread Unity.

261
00:16:04,119 --> 00:16:05,435
SUPERGIRL: Sorry.

262
00:16:07,890 --> 00:16:09,590
Road's closed.

263
00:16:20,236 --> 00:16:22,548
[GRUNTING]

264
00:16:22,572 --> 00:16:24,799
Give up the fight, child.

265
00:16:24,823 --> 00:16:27,369
Forces mightier than you couldn't stop us.

266
00:16:27,393 --> 00:16:29,059
Let me try.

267
00:16:31,831 --> 00:16:33,881
[ALL GROANING]

268
00:16:42,775 --> 00:16:45,926
[ALL GROANING]

269
00:16:52,601 --> 00:16:53,951
[GRUNTING]

270
00:16:57,139 --> 00:16:58,788
[GROWLING]

271
00:17:18,244 --> 00:17:20,889
You are nothing.

272
00:17:20,913 --> 00:17:24,448
Behold the true power of Unity.

273
00:17:37,263 --> 00:17:38,862
Superman!

274
00:17:42,184 --> 00:17:43,500
[GASPS]

275
00:17:58,000 --> 00:17:59,132
[SCREAMS]

276
00:18:06,342 --> 00:18:10,544
Together, we will force your subjugation.

277
00:18:16,852 --> 00:18:18,502
No, you don't!

278
00:18:27,196 --> 00:18:29,446
[SCREAMING]

279
00:19:22,918 --> 00:19:25,569
[GROANING]

280
00:19:37,282 --> 00:19:38,243
Kara?

281
00:19:38,267 --> 00:19:40,511
Shh.

282
00:19:40,535 --> 00:19:42,363
Not so loud, Pa.

283
00:19:42,387 --> 00:19:44,204
Let's go.

284
00:19:49,695 --> 00:19:50,671
[MOOING]

285
00:19:50,695 --> 00:19:52,007
[CLUCKING]

286
00:19:52,031 --> 00:19:56,178
And we were actually part of some alien conspiracy?

287
00:19:56,202 --> 00:19:57,612
Yeah, Pa.

288
00:19:57,636 --> 00:19:59,486
And you were crankier than usual.

289
00:20:00,806 --> 00:20:02,901
But I can't tell you how great it is

290
00:20:02,925 --> 00:20:04,691
to have everything back to normal.

291
00:20:06,095 --> 00:20:08,223
I thought you found normal boring.

292
00:20:08,247 --> 00:20:11,142
Well, at this point, boring's not so bad.

293
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:13,417
I'm even meeting Owen down at the comic store.

294
00:20:15,687 --> 00:20:17,849
Say, Martha, did you see what the Langs are growin'?

295
00:20:17,873 --> 00:20:19,083
Looks like rutabaga.

296
00:20:19,107 --> 00:20:20,535
MARTHA: I don't know, Jonathan.

297
00:20:20,559 --> 00:20:22,003
Looks like turnips to me.

298
00:20:22,027 --> 00:20:23,326
[SIGHS]

299
00:20:27,823 --> 00:20:30,457
♪

